        <updateDate>2022-01-18T23:08:30Z</updateDate>
        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><strong>Parity Implementation Assistance Act</strong></p> <p>This bill provides grants to assist states with the implementation of the federal mental health parity requirements. States receiving the grants must request and review from private health insurance plans their required comparative analysis of nonquantitative treatment limitations (NQTLs) with respect to mental health or substance use disorder benefits. (NQTLs are limitations on the scope or duration of benefits for treatment, such as preauthorization requirements.)</p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
